The C library is maintained separately. Fetch it from
https://github.com/GregorR/musl , branch 'microcosm'.

To build Microcosm:

0 (if necessary)) Adjust your paths (. use.sh)

1) Build the cross-compiler (cd cross ; ./buildcc.sh)

2) Build libmicrocosm (cd libmicrocosm ; make ; make install)

3) Build the dynamic loader
    cd gelfload
    ./configure --prefix=/opt/microcosm
    make all install

4) Build the C library, musl (cd musl ; cp ../musl.config.mak config.mak ; make all install)

5) Symlink the C library into the dynamic loader's path
    mkdir -p /opt/microcosm/lib/microcosm
    ln -s /opt/cross/x86_64-pc-microcosm/x86_64-pc-microcosm/lib/libc.so /opt/microcosm/lib/microcosm/libc.so

6) Build the host library
    cd libmicrocosm_host
    ./configure --target=x86_64-pc-microcosm --prefix=<somewhere you can load .so files from>
    make all install

7) Run stuff
    x86_64-pc-microcosm-gcc my-favorite-c-program.c
    /opt/microcosm/bin/microcosm ./a.out
